					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5837071#post-3794116</guid>
				<title>Re: Is this a joke?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5837071/spc-1057#post-3794116</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 08 May 2018 15:30:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Captain Kirby</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3440103</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Just to clear up any confusion, technically, I've put this with all the -J SCPs. Honestly, for all intents and purposes, it is a -j (even has it in the URL) kinda following suit of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/spc-173-j">SPC-173-J</a> and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/spc-2935-j">SPC-2935-J</a>. I just don't include the -J in the article because well&#8230; its already SPC, the -J feels redundant.</p> <p>I don't just call it an SPC article though because I'm pretty sure they have their own GOI format-type-thing, and this is not using that format.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
